\ it ( -- v ) / other ( -- v ) / them ( -- v1 v0 ) — anaphora, with aliases
\ this = it, that = other: the stack top (top two) as the current scope began.
\ At top level the scope is the line (the entry snapshot); inside a colon
\ definition it is the word's activation, bound at entry as hidden locals
\ ((enter-anaphors) frame). Pinned per scope, non-consuming, repeatable,
\ value capture (survives the scope consuming the operand).

\ === it: pinned at line start ===
5
it . cr                \ 5
it it + . cr           \ 10
1 + it + . cr          \ 11 (the line consumed the 5; it still names it)
clear

\ === them: the top two, original order ===
3 4
them + . cr            \ 7
them - . cr            \ -1
them swap - . cr       \ 1
clear

\ === pushes during the line don't move it ===
9
100 it + . cr          \ 109
clear

\ === clear then it recovers the pre-line top ===
1 2
clear it . cr          \ 2
clear

\ === a failed line restores the stack; it is unchanged after ===
8
1 0 %
it . cr                \ 8
clear

\ === heap values alias, like dup ===
[ 1 2 3 ]
it size . cr           \ 3
it 0 @i . cr           \ 1
clear

\ === other: the second entry value; this/that alias it/other ===
3 4
other . cr             \ 3
this . cr              \ 4
that . cr              \ 3
this that - . cr       \ 1
clear

\ === definitions: it is the entry TOS, pinned per activation ===
: square it it * ;
5 square . cr          \ 25
: late 2 * it + ;
10 late . cr           \ 30 (the body consumed the 10; it still names it)
clear

\ === definitions: them / other / aliases ===
: diff them - ;
3 4 diff . cr          \ -1
: under other ;
7 8 under . cr         \ 7
: aliased this that + ;
1 2 aliased . cr       \ 3
clear

\ === it then them in one body (three compile passes) ===
: upgrade it them + + ;
3 4 upgrade . cr       \ 11
clear

\ === peek before receive: it and a receive see the same value ===
: mixed | >x | it x + ;
6 mixed . cr           \ 12
: allrec |> x y | it x + y - ;
10 3 4 allrec . cr     \ 3 (it = y = 4)
clear

\ === quotations inherit the definition's binding ===
: quoted [ 1 2 3 ] [: drop it :] map ;
9 quoted . cr          \ [ 9 9 9 ]
clear

\ === early exit unwinds the anaphor frame ===
: early it 5 > if "big" exit then it 2 * ;
9 early . cr           \ big
3 early . cr           \ 6
clear

\ === recursion rebinds per activation ===
: countdown it 0 > if it 1 - countdown then ;
3 countdown .s cr      \ 3 2 1 0 (it is non-consuming; one entry value per activation)
clear

\ === inline splice captures at the call site ===
: sq it it * ; inline
: user 1 + sq ;
4 user . cr            \ 25
clear

\ === see shows the typed source; see-compiled shows the frame ===
' square see
' square see-compiled

\ === with user locals: one fused frame, anaphors and locals all level 0 ===
: mixed | >x | it it * x + ;
5 3 mixed . cr         \ 12 (it = 3 = x; 9 + 3)
drop
' mixed see-compiled
clear

\ === a local named it shadows the anaphor ===
: shadowed | >it | it 100 + ;
1 shadowed . cr        \ 101
clear

\ === top-level quotations keep the dynamic entry meaning ===
5
[: it :] execute . cr  \ 5
clear

\ === errors (too few values at scope entry) ===
it                     \ (empty at line start)
them                   \ (empty at line start)
7
them                   \ (one value at line start; them needs 2)
other                  \ (one value at line start; other needs 2)
clear
: strict it ;
strict                 \ (empty stack at word entry)
: strict2 them + ;
9 strict2              \ (one value at word entry; them needs 2)
